    Overview - The Halifax Group       Investor LoginHalifax Brochure Search for:    Overview Print  The Halifax Group is a private investment firm dedicated to partnering with founders and managers of lower middle-market businesses with total enterprise values generally between $50 million and $250 million. Our principals bring decades of experience and appreciate the unique complexities of emerging businesses.Dependable collaboratorsWith value-added expertiseAnd a proven track recordHalifax is committed to a personal, collaborative approach to partnering with owners and managers.The firm’s principals have a wealth of investment and operating experience in business services, franchising, health and wellness, and infrastructure services.Halifax is comprised of 18 professionals with a combined 100+ years of investing experience with global firms.   More Information ForEntrepreneursIntermediariesInvestors  © 2017 The Halifax Group. All rights reserved. Neither The Halifax Group nor its affiliates provides investment advisory services to the public. Strengthened by Alliant Studios   
    Investment Philosophy - The Halifax Group       Investor LoginHalifax Brochure Search for:    Investment Philosophy Print  The cornerstone of The Halifax Group’s investment approach is partnership. We partner with strong management teams or entrepreneurs with a distinguished track record of success in highly fragmented industries.  Since 1999, our principals have invested alongside entrepreneurs and managers in 27 platform companies with committed capital from our world-class institutional investor base.With offices in Washington, DC, Dallas, TX and Raleigh, NC, Halifax typically invests $25 to $75 million in leading businesses generally within the Business Services, Health and Wellness, Infrastructure and Franchising industry sectors.Partnership equityDependable collaborators • With a proven track record • And more than $1 billion committed capitalWe invest not only capital, but our time, resources and relationships to execute a shared strategy for growth. In the past, we have achieved success by:Adding infrastructure to provide operating leverageIdentifying and helping execute add-on acquisitionsSupporting management through expanded teams that share a common vision for growthExpanding sales channels through strategic partnerships with other companies within the portfolioCollaborating on business strategy development   More Information ForEntrepreneursIntermediariesInvestors  © 2017 The Halifax Group. All rights reserved. Neither The Halifax Group nor its affiliates provides investment advisory services to the public. Strengthened by Alliant Studios   
